Privacy Policy for RecLink

Last Updated: 07/04/25

1. Introduction
Welcome to RecLink! This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when using our Discord bot. By using RecLink, you agree to the data practices described in this policy.

2. Information We Collect
RecLink may collect the following types of information:
- Discord User IDs to identify and respond to users.
- Rec Room profile information as retrieved from Rec Room’s API.
- Server-related data, such as server IDs, for bot functionality.
- Interaction logs to improve service quality and troubleshoot issues.

3. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data to:
- Provide Rec Room-related information and bot functionality.
- Improve RecLink’s performance and troubleshoot errors.
- Enforce rules and prevent abuse of the bot.
- Comply with legal obligations when required.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
- We do not sell or share your data with third parties.
- Data may be shared with Rec Room’s API service for retrieving requested information.
- Data may be disclosed if required by law or to prevent malicious activity.

5. Data Storage and Security
- We take reasonable security measures to protect your data.
- Data is stored only as long as necessary for functionality.
- If you wish to remove your data, make a ticket in the RecLink discord server.

6. Third-Party Services
- RecLink interacts with Rec Room’s API, which has its own privacy policies.
- We are not responsible for data handling by external services such as Discord or Rec Room.

7. Changes to This Policy
- We may update this privacy policy at any time.
- Continued use of RecLink after updates constitutes acceptance of the new policy.

8. Contact
For questions or data removal requests, contact the support team at the RecLink discord server.

By using RecLink, you acknowledge and agree to this privacy policy.

